        "text": "Everything said is based on the assumption that a commonality of vital interests can be increasingly grasped: thus the realization that security is only attainable as security on a reciprocal basis; that it must be a common goal to prevent innovations in the field of weapons technology; that all participants must refrain from giving nuclear conflict a higher consecration. If this can be thought of as attainable, the hope is not far-fetched that another, perhaps the decisive condition for building trust could come about: the hope that we could learn to see the endangerment of human lives on this side and on the other side of the borders in context. The lightning extinction by nuclear force, whoever it hits or doesn't hit, is a universal catastrophe. It brings into the world a new way of killing and being killed that drops all people into an immeasurable new vulnerability. The emotional insight that this is so may help to overcome the limitations of our capacity for consternation. What is hoped for here is not the good man, but a new power of our imagination.\n"
